guide: 7You will gain passive progress in this
7by having a pet equipped at all times.
7Even a Lvl 100 pet counts for this.
7You should use SkyHanni's Trapper features
7to make this easier. Use /warp trapper
7to get back to Trevor whenever you want.
7You will need a bow for this.
7Visit the Campfire in The Park and do
7the Trial of Fire. (140 dps over 10s)
7You will need 160 Dark Oak and 1k Spruce
7in the progress of this.
7Enchant your Ender Armor with Growth 5
7and if you still struggle, reforge it
7to Titanic at the Blacksmith.
7You can also use the Wand of Healing.
7Talk to Jax in the Hub
7under the Weaponsmith
7and complete on of his challenges.
7You should buy an Artisanal Shortbow
7for this.
7You should either kill Endermen in
7End using your Void Sword (200k) and
7Ender Armor for this (buy the Ender Training
7Perk from Tyzzo next to the Draconic Altar)
7or Spiders in the Spiders Den with a Cleave 5
7weapon. You might want to also use the free
7Combat XP from Bestiary Miletones for this.
7Can be made from Lapis Lazuli Collection 5 (10k),
7a drop from fishing, from the Experimentation Table,
7and dropped from Ender Nodes in the End (11-13% chance).
7Kill Team Treasurite members in the Crystal Hollows.
7They spawn in the Mithril Deposits and you will need
7Heart of the Mountain 4 to go there.
7Wear Ender Armor enchanted with Growth 5
7and wear it in The End.
7You can also enchant Mushroom Armor like that
7and wear it in The Garden.
7Growth 5 requires Enchanting Level 5
7and costs 50 Experience Levels per piece.
7Reforge your armor to Titanic if needed.
7Brew a Speed Potion by using either Enchanted Sugar
7or an Enchanted Sugar Cane. If you use the Sugar, you'll
7need to combine the brewed potion with a Glowstone.
7You can get that Glowstone by buying one block
7from the Builder and breaking it on your island.
7You can get the Enchanted Sugar (Cane) from farming
7Sugar Cane or killing pests in the Garden.
7Kill Sheeps in the Desert Island (/warp desert)
7place as many Sheep Minions as you can and
7give them the best fuel and storage you have
7access to. Remember to collect them in time.
7Talk to Guildford in the Dungeon Hub
7and complete 4/4 objectives for 3 races.
7Don't forget to talk to Guildford
7after each run you do.
7Grab the Fairy Souls you run across while
7doing this Bingo. You can use NEU (/neusouls on)
7or TimeDeo's Tutorials on YouTube for help.
7Kill mobs with a weapon that you have
7Scavenger 3+ applied to.
7For this you should utilize the Garden.
7Melons will unlock at Garden Level 6.
7Use the Gardening Axe and its upgrade once you
7unlock Melons. You might want to save some copper
7to enchant the axe with Sunder.
7You will most likely get this passively.
7Talk to Bramass Beastslayer in The Spiders Den.
7Use /be ingame to view your progress once you did that.
7You can unlock 17/17 Farming Collections,
76/11 Combat Collections, 6/6 Foraging Collections,
714/22 Mining Collections for a total of 43 collections.
7You will also get some Fishing Collections.
7Do commissions and events in The Dwarven Mines,
7claim your daily powder from the Puzzler and
7from giving Fetchur the items he asks for.
7Fetchurs items are all listed in the Wiki.
7Try to do those while a '2x Powder' event is active.
7You might want to use the Royal Reforge on your
7equipment to gain more powder from events.
7You can also fish up and kill Mithril Grubbers
7in the Abandoned Quarry (Fishing 6).
7Recommended for this either Revenant Horror II
7or Tarantula Broodfather II. Use your Ender Armor
7and Void Sword (200k) for this.
7To progress in this you can:
7- Participate in Dragon Fights
7- Salvage Ender Pieces at the Draconic Altar
7- Kill Lost Adventurers
7- Collect secrets in dungeons
7This unlocks at 5k Diamond Collection. Use Pure Ores
7in the Dwarven Mines for this. Craft it with
71 Enchanted Diamond and 8 Vines (costs 40 Jungle Leaves,
7requires Jungle Wood Collection 4 to unlock it in /trades.)
7fNo eggs:
7Dolphin, Bee, Grandma Wolf, Bingo, Rock, Owl,
7Enderman, Tarantula and Oringo pets
7fEggs needed:
7Jerry, Rabbit, Pig, Chicken, Bat, Silverfish
7To get the Enchanted Eggs needed, kill Chickens
7in The Barn till you get the Chicken Head recipe.
7Once you get your first Enchanted Egg, put it into
7one Chicken Minion to generate more of those over time.
7You will most likely get this from leveling up
7skills for the Skill Average goal.
7Remember to actually put the money
7you get in the Bank :)
7Use the wiki to figure out what Fetchur asks for.
7You will need to get into Dwarven Mines to be
7able to even talk to him.
7For this you'll want to open structure chests
7in the Crystal Hollows, do a Nucleus Run
7(you will need a Small Gemstone Sack for this to count)
7or kill Worms/Scathas.
7For this you need to place down a Chum Bucket
7while fishing. It's recommended to use a Chum Rod
7as this will gain quicker progress.
7Purchase it from Moby on the Desert Island.
7cDon't forget to actually deposit the Chum you fish ;)
7For this you will need Combat 15.
7To blow up crypts you can use
7class abilities (Tank, Archer, Mage)
7and/or Superboom TNTs that drop
7from slaying Minibosses in dungeons
7and can be bought from Walther in
7The Deep Caverns or Ophelia in
7The Dungeon Hub.
7You can buy this for a total of 400 coins
7from the Fishing Merchant in the Hub.
7For this you'll want to open structure chests
7in the Crystal Hollows, do a Nucleus Run
7(you will need a Small Gemstone Sack for this to count)
7or kill Worms/Scathas.
7Talk to the Blacksmith in the Hub
7and gamble Reforges on an armor piece
7until you get the Titanic Reforge.
7You might need to bring some money for this.
7Kill farm animals in the Barn with a Cleaver
7with Cleave 5 and Sharpness 5
7or spiders in Arachne's Burrow
7in the Spider's Den with a Dreadlord Sword.
7You can also kill Endermen in The End to
7get progress towards the
7Enderman Slayer Community Goal.
7This unlocks at 5k Diamond Collection. Use Pure Ores
7in the Dwarven Mines for this. Craft it with
71 Enchanted Diamond and 8 Vines (costs 40 Jungle Leaves,
7requires Jungle Wood Collection 4 to unlock it in /trades.)
7Recommended for this is to fish in the
7Backwater Bayou with the best rod you have
7access to and full Angler Set or better.
7You can also donate any special fish that you
7get to Coral in Galatea (requires 1.21.5)
7You'll unlock this recipe passively
7(2.5k leather collection)
7if you chose to do Exterminator in Barn.
7Craft it with 592 Leather.
7You can also use Cow Minions for this.
7Do your daily Experimentation Tables
7after getting Enchanting Level 10.
7Mine Pure Emeralds in the Dwarven Mines
7with a Fortune 3+ pickaxe.
7You might want to use as many minions
7as you have access to for this.
7Remember to put a compactor in the minions
7when you plan on leaving for a while.
7Don't forget to fuel the minions,
7give them storages and collect them in time.
7To help with this, try to make bigger crafts
7by hand for Carpentry levels.
7Also do your daily experiments and make sure
7to have a pet active at all times
7(any pet works, even level 100).
7You will most likely get this passively.
7Use /be ingame to view your progress once you
7talked to Bramass Beastslayer in The Spiders Den.
7Kill Team Treasurite members in the Crystal Hollows.
7They spawn in the Mithril Deposits and you will need
7Heart of the Mountain 4 to go there.
7For this you may want to participate
7in Mining Events in the Dwarven Mines
7as you have a 20% chance to obtain
7an Ultimate Enchanted Book from this.
7You can also open Dungeon Reward Chests
7for this. For that way you may require coins.
7Craft Leather, Iron, Gold and Diamond Armor.
7Recommended for this are:
7Bingo, Rock and Grandma Wolf.
7Talk to Guildford in the Dungeon Hub
7and complete 4/4 objectives for 3 races.
7Don't forget to talk to Guildford
7after each run you do.
7Start an Entrance floor and play Mage/Tank/Berserker to use
7the classes abilities to kill a Lost Adventurer.
7You only need to get the last hit
7on it to count, so you can get help from your team.
7You need Combat Level 15 to join a Dungeon.
7Apply/Use the highest tier of Scavenger
7that you can get your hands on and put it
7on your main weapon. Gifts from the Jerry Island
7can be a way to obtain Scavenger IV books.
7You can also use the weapon drops from dungeon mobs
7as those have guaranteed Scavenger 5.
7For this you can farm some crops
7in the Hub or do a bit of farming
7in The Garden (needs SB Level 12).
7Craft some easy minions while also getting
7those that will help with this Bingo.
7(meaning Cow, Gold, Emerald and maybe
7Fishing Minion if you want to go for
7Community Goals later)
7Mine Pure Gold in the Dwarven Mines
7or Gold Blocks in the Mines of Divan
7(found in the Crystal Hollows,
7needs HOTM 4 to enter)
7with a Fortune 3+ pickaxe.
7You might want to use as many minions
7as you have access to for this.
7Remember to put a compactor in the minions
7when you plan on leaving for a while.
7Don't forget to fuel the minions,
7give them storages and collect them in time.
7You can find Relic Coordinates in Skytils or the Wiki.
7You will need Ender Pearls to reach some of them.
7Get yourself a splash, equip a Bingo Pet
7and get the cake buff by eating the cakes
7on xMeru's, skyerzz's or prtl's island.
7If this doesn't finish it, get a Void Sword (200k) in the End
7and hold it while some Ender Armor and/or Equipment.
7Kill Endermen in The End using full Ender Armor
7and a Void Sword or Dreadlord Sword.
